# Q5 hybrid: small fixtures regenerated each test run; only the
# perf fixture and the rare hand-authored fixture are committed.
#
# The 6 xlsx-6 fixtures (clean.xlsx, encrypted.xlsx, hidden_first.xlsx,
# merged.xlsx, multi_sheet.xlsx, with_legacy.xlsx) are produced by
# `tests/regenerate_synthetic_inputs.py` and intentionally NOT
# tracked; they live on the developer's filesystem only.
#
# `macro.xlsm` is hand-authored (xlsx-6 m-E DEVIATION; see ../README.md)
# and IS committed.
#
# `huge-100k-rows.{xlsx,rules.json}` is the xlsx-7 perf fixture
# (committed per Q5=hybrid; generated by ../inputs/_generate.py
# --regenerate-perf-fixture, deterministic seed 42).

*

!.gitignore
!macro.xlsm
!huge-100k-rows.xlsx
!huge-100k-rows.rules.json
!huge-100k-rows-10rules.rules.json
